                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/983: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-06T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Your no. 51, dated July 5, 5 p.m. I had an interview with President Leguía
                    this morning at the end of which he expressed <pb facs="0620" n="500"
                        xml:id="pg_500"/> himself as being in favor of accepting the suggestion as
                    it is. He is consulting the Cabinet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
